<issue
   id="RBN-1"
   type="mapping_table"
   linkend="ae entity=Envelope aa attribute=acknowledge"
   status="closed"
   category="editorial"
   by="Rob Bodington"
   date="03-01-13">
<description>
  <p>
    The mapping should reflect the values of acknowledge:
    "" (blank), "ask message arrival" or "ask message read".
  </p>
  <p>
    The mapping of ARM entity attributes should start at the entity that
    the ARM entity has been mapped to
  </p>
  <p>
    envelope &lt;= 
    [product
    product.name
    {(product.name = '')
     (product.name = 'ask message arrival')
     (product.name = 'ask message read')}
    [characterized_object]
  </p>
</description>

<comment
   by="Sean Barker" 
   date="03-01-13">
<description>
As per issue, except that the values 'acknowledge arrival' and 'delivery failure' also
included, and map for id also defined in similar way.
</description>
</comment>
</issue>


